33:03.807 --> 33:05.766
- No.

33:05.809 --> 33:07.463
[speaks Hebrew]

33:09.770 --> 33:11.641
- Let them in, Rosamie.

33:18.997 --> 33:21.956
- How many other women?

33:22.000 --> 33:24.654
- At least two others
that we know of,

33:24.698 --> 33:27.005
but probably dozens more.

33:33.315 --> 33:36.144
- Your daughter's beautiful.
- [sighs]

33:36.188 --> 33:38.103
Thank God
she looks like Rosamie.

33:38.146 --> 33:40.496
[chuckling]

33:41.193 --> 33:42.542
I was a wedding pianist.

33:42.585 --> 33:45.371
Rosamie
was a catering waitress.

33:45.414 --> 33:49.375
She liked my songs and laughed
at all of my dopey stories.

33:49.418 --> 33:50.854
[chuckles]

33:50.898 --> 33:54.336
Maybe she was not acceptable
to some of my relatives

33:54.380 --> 33:59.689
at the Neil Sedaka end
of Ocean Parkway, but--[sighs]

33:59.733 --> 34:03.824
She was the woman
of my simple dreams.

34:03.867 --> 34:06.435
She converted,
so I married her

34:06.479 --> 34:10.135
and we had a beautiful baby.

34:12.615 --> 34:15.966
And so--
[plays note on piano]

34:16.010 --> 34:17.577
And so...

34:19.187 --> 34:22.712
Tell me why you're here,
